    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the northern Brisbane market and what buyers are comparing when they look at Bridgeman Downs. The suburb competes directly with Carseldine and Aspley for family demand, and understanding that comparison is critical to positioning your campaign correctly.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Bridgeman Downs sits north of Carseldine Road and east of Samford Road, with bus routes connecting to the northern busway corridor and Westfield Chermside within easy reach. Padua College is one of Brisbane's most respected private schools and draws families specifically to this northern pocket. Homes on the larger allotments in the western and northern sections of the suburb consistently achieve a premium over the suburb median, particularly where the land allows for future improvements or pool additions. The suburb's owner-occupier demographic means stock is tightly held and well-maintained, which supports pricing stability when conditions are right.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
